mediaNotes: This individual repeatedly gave a song type that I've never heard in this species before. The song type includes a short trill either at or near the end of the song. Songs with this trill are audible at 2:00, 3:06, 3:30, 3:48, 5:09, and 10:36 of this recording. Also worth noting in this recording is the variability in song length, with several songs lasting nearly 3 seconds in length (in excess of the maximum duration noted in the Birds of North America account).
Habitat: Mixed Coniferous/Deciduous.
